<p>The <i>perlcgi</i> framework can be used to run <i>any</i> CGI script, but, like the <xref href="index.dita">perl</xref> framework, it provides ActivePerl in the default PATH and supports module installation via <xref href="index.dita">PPM</xref> and <xref href="index.dita">
<i>cpanm</i>
</xref>.</p>
<p>Unlike the perl framework, setting the <xref href="../../../../../../devplatform/helion/user/deploy/1.1manifestyml.dita#start-file" >
<i>start-file</i>
</xref> option
has no effect, as there is no permanently running application. A new
instance of a CGI script is started for each request.</p>
<p>Perl scripts deployed with this framework should begin with:</p>
<codeblock>
  <codeph>#!/usr/bin/env perl
</codeph>
</codeblock>
